# Database & Real Email Integration

This plan outlines the steps to replace the temporary JSON-based data store and mock email service with a robust PostgreSQL database (via Prisma) and a real email provider (Resend).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Environment Variables Setup**: Before we can fully execute this plan, you will need to create two accounts (they both have generous free tiers):
> 1. **Database**: Create a PostgreSQL database (I recommend [Neon.tech](https://neon.tech/) or [Supabase](https://supabase.com/)). You will need the `DATABASE_URL` connection string.
> 2. **Email API**: Create a free account at [Resend](https://resend.com/) and generate an API key. You will need the `RESEND_API_KEY`.
> 
> Once you have these, you'll add them to your `.env` or `.env.local` file. I can guide you through this if needed!

## Proposed Changes

### Dependencies
- Install database tools: `prisma` (dev dependency), `@prisma/client`
- Install email tools: `resend`

### Database & Prisma Schema

#### [NEW] prisma/schema.prisma
We will initialize Prisma and create a schema that supports users with hashed passwords and verification tokens.

```prisma
datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
  url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
}

generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client-js"
}

model User {
  id                String   @id @default(cuid())
  email             String   @unique
  passwordHash      String
  isVerified        Boolean  @default(false)
  verificationToken String?  @unique
  createdAt         DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt         DateTime @updatedAt
}
```

#### [NEW] src/lib/prisma.ts
Create a singleton instance of the Prisma client to avoid connection limits during development (a common Next.js issue).

---

### Data Access Layer Updates

#### [MODIFY] src/lib/users.ts
We will rewrite the functions in this file to interact with the PostgreSQL database via Prisma instead of the local `users.json` file.
- `findUserByEmail` -> queries Prisma
- `createUser` -> creates record in Prisma
- `updateUser` -> updates record in Prisma
- `findUserByVerificationToken` -> queries Prisma

---

### Email Integration

#### [MODIFY] src/lib/mailer.ts
We will replace the `nodemailer` / Ethereal Email implementation with the official `resend` Node.js SDK.

- Initialize `const resend = new Resend(process.env.RESEND_API_KEY)`
- Update `sendVerificationEmail` to use `resend.emails.send(...)`

---

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  **Environment Setup**: User provides `DATABASE_URL` and `RESEND_API_KEY`.
2.  **Database Migration**: Run `npx prisma db push` to sync the schema to the live database.
3.  **Registration Flow**: Register a new user via the UI.
4.  **Database Check**: Verify the user record appears in the PostgreSQL database with `isVerified: false`.
5.  **Email Check**: Verify that a real email arrives at the registered email address.
6.  **Verification Flow**: Click the link in the email and ensure the user's database record updates to `isVerified: true`.
7.  **Login**: Successfully log in with the verified credentials.
